BELIEVE your man when he says he&rsquo;s going to the tavern to play soccer!When guys go to PK&rsquo;s Tavern in Mandela Park, Khayelitsha they are not just there to booze. The tavern is not just a drinking hole &ndash; many guys who go there play street soccer.PK&rsquo;s Tavern has a team that takes part in the Smirnoff Raga Bolo championship. Speaking to Daily Sun, coach Jones Mkentane said they started taking part in 2011 and have so far won the tournament twice &ndash; in 2012 and 2016.Player Luxolo Lewu (31) said street soccer helped them to keep fit.&ldquo;It&rsquo;s a social league. We keep ourselves busy and healthy. We normally play after hours. &ldquo;We do not have much time to train but whenever we play we are always sharp.&rdquo; Tavern owner Lawrence &ldquo;TK&rdquo; Stamper said the league changed many people&rsquo;s lives.&ldquo;I have supported this initiative since it was started in 2011. Soccer takes people away from wrong things. It helps them avoid drugs and criminal activities.&rdquo;